==English==

===Etymology===
From {{OF.}} ''[[-iste]]'' and {{L.}} ''[[-ista]]''

===Suffix===
'''-ist'''

[[Category:English suffixes|ist]]
Added to words to form nouns denoting:
#one who follows a [[principle]]
#:Marx'''ist'''
#:Note, this is related to [[-ism]], e.g. Marx'''ism'''
#a member of a profession or one interested in something
#:botan'''ist'''
#:psychiatr'''ist''', ''one who studies psychiatry''
#a person who uses something
#:violin'''ist''', ''one who plays a violin''
#a person who holds [[prejudiced]] views
#:sex'''ist'''
#:rac'''ist'''

